  "body": "Working on upgrading rollup - some test builds show decreasing in size of bundles.\r\nBut also there are some problems with it:\r\n\r\n1. The `legacy` option is now deprecated, so is it critical for building **react** ?\r\nI checked this [issue](https://github.com/rollup/rollup/issues/2135) - and it tells that it's totally fine.\r\n2. There are couples **circular dependency** warnings with `ReactFiberScheduler.js`  and also some **default' is not exported** warnings\r\n\r\nYou also can check my [branch](https://github.com/mmarkelov/react/tree/Upgrade_Rollup)\r\nMaybe you can help me with it\r\n\r\nSo what do you think about this? Does that make sense?\r\n",
